"""Database module for the litigation-context MCP server.

Provides connection management, document CRUD, FTS5 search, knowledge graph
loading, evolution pipeline, and system diagnostics against litigation_context.db.

Architecture:
    get_connection() → sqlite3.Connection (WAL, 60s busy_timeout, 32MB cache)
    All public functions accept ``conn`` as first parameter.
    _CircuitBreaker protects against cascading DB failures.
    HealthStatus singleton tracks server health across the MCP lifespan.

Usage::

    conn = get_connection()
    try:
        stats = get_stats(conn)
        results = search_pages(conn, "custody", limit=10)
    finally:
        conn.close()
"""

